query: S1=>(@p Person:*); RETURN * LIMIT 20
S1=>(@s *)-[@r *]->(@o *); RETURN s.label AS Sub, UCOUNT(r.rel) AS Relation, o.label AS Obj
S1=>(@P1 Person:*); RETURN P1.NodeFor AS NodeFor, COUNT(P1.name) AS "Customers Below 18", P1.AgeAtRegistration AS Age_Registration EXCLUDE_GROUPBY(Age_Registration) WHERE Age_Registration < 18
S1=>(@P1 Person:*); RETURN P1.NodeFor AS NodeFor, COUNT(P1.name) AS "Customers Above 65", P1.AgeAtRegistration AS Age_Registration EXCLUDE_GROUPBY(Age_Registration) WHERE Age_Registration >= 65
S1=>(@P Person:* {DATE_YEAR($CreatedDate+0)= 2022});RETURN P.NodeFor, COUNT(P.name) AS Total_Users
S1=>(@P Person:* {DATE_YEAR($CreatedDate+0)=2022 AND DATE_MONTH($CreatedDate+0)=9});RETURN P.NodeFor AS NodeFor, COUNT(P.name) AS Total_Users
S1=>(@P Person:* {NodeFor = "Customer" AND DATE_YEAR($CreatedDate+0) = 2022 AND DATE_MONTH($CreatedDate+0) >= 8 AND DATE_MONTH($CreatedDate+0) <= 9});RETURN COUNT(P.name) AS Total_Customer

S1=>(@P Person:* {NodeFor = "Customer" AND DATE_YEAR($CreatedDate+0) = 2022 AND DATE_MONTH($CreatedDate+0) = 9 AND DATE_DAY($CreatedDate+0) >= 1 AND DATE_DAY($CreatedDate+0) <= 15});RETURN COUNT(P.name) AS Total_Customer

S1=>(@P1 Person:* {NodeFor="Customer"})-[@s IS_IN_STATE]->(@S State:Assam)]; RETURN S.name AS State, s.District, P1.name AS Customer, P1.CreatedDate , P1.DOB, P1.Gender, P1.AgeAtRegistration AS Age_Registration, P1.LangType AS LangType LIMIT 200
S1=>(@P1 Person:*)-[@s IS_IN_STATE {District = Datia}]->(@S State:*)]; RETURN s.District AS District, S.name AS State, COUNT(P1.name) AS total_customer
S1=>(@P1 Person:*)-[@s IS_IN_STATE]->(@S State:Assam)]; RETURN S.name AS State, COUNT(P1.name) AS total_customer, UCOUNT(s.District) AS District
S1=>(@P1 Person:* {NodeFor="Customer"})-[@h HAS_PINCODE]->(@Z Pincode:848213); RETURN UCOUNT(P1.name) AS Unique_Customers, Z.name AS Pincode
S1=>(@P Person:* {BusinessCategory !~ NA});RETURN P.BusinessCategory AS BusinessCategory, UCOUNT(P.name) AS Unique_Customer
s1=>(@P1 Person:* {NodeFor = "Customer"})-[HAS_FAMILY_MEMBER]->(@P2 Person:* {NodeFor = "Family_Member"});RETURN UCOUNT(P1.name) AS customers
S1=>(@P1 Person:* {NodeFor = "Customer"})-[HAS_FAMILY_MEMBER]->(@P2 Person:* {NodeFor = "Family_Member"});RETURN COUNT(P2.name) AS Members, P2.Gender
S1=>(@P Person:* {NodeFor = "Customer"})-[@r HAS_FAMILY_MEMBER]->(@p Person:* {NodeFor = "Family_Member"});RETURN r.RelationShipValue AS Relation, COUNT(p.name) AS "Total Count"
S1=>(@P Person:* {NodeFor = "Family_Member"});RETURN COUNT(P.name) AS "Total Family Members"
S1=>(@P Person:* {Profession !~ NA AND NodeFor="Customer"});RETURN P.Profession AS Profession, COUNT(P.name) AS Unique_Customer
S1=>(@P Person:* {BusinessCategory !~ NA});RETURN P.BusinessCategory AS BusinessCategory, UCOUNT(P.name) AS Unique_Customer
S1=>(@P Person:* {Education !~ NA});RETURN P.Education AS Education, COUNT(P.name) AS Unique_Customer
S1=>(@P Person:* {Income !~ NA});RETURN P.Income AS Income, UCOUNT(P.name) AS Unique_Customer
